{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how per-term coverage in AC1 proof command will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f449672ba4e123120","f154be3f6c8ae70e7","f2fa895763e33c7e2","fa0b5529d5f276b60","fa287b0359c65819a","f3a2162dac9cac61a","fc5753f10570a2f70","fe9da58eaf2876ed1","f263b01ce558c2136"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"per-term coverage in AC1 proof command"},{"coaching":"Plan how completeness gap in AC2 proof for --force will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f7df13d4b65d1142f"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"completeness gap in AC2 proof for --force"},{"coaching":"Plan how semantic coverage in AC3 section-header proof will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f50af9fae197d5693","fb7041b7ae54918ad"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"semantic coverage in AC3 section-header proof"},{"coaching":"Pin down dispatch/gate/validate idea-status lifecycle semantics with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f848f705a8e67999b"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"dispatch/gate/validate idea-status lifecycle semantics"},{"coaching":"Plan how acceptance-criteria verification strategy overall will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"acceptance-criteria verification strategy overall"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":14,"blocking":0,"dropped":9,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":5,"ran":true,"references":5,"resolved":4,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":1},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":3991,"file_impact":4,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":41,"verify_lint_abstained":41},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1012,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":4,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":213.4,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":572561.6,"total_ms":572876.9,"verify_requests":24},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Replace the `rg -c` alternation count in AC1's proving command with four separate `rg -q` checks (one per required term) so all four concepts must be present independently.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"[ \\\"$(rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md)\\\" -ge 4 ]\" — counts matching lines via alternation, not distinct concept occurrences","Defect type: cardinality assertion does not correctly measure that each of the four required terms appears at least once"],"finding":"AC1's proving command uses `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags'` which returns the count of LINES that match the alternation (any one of the four terms), not the count of distinct concepts covered. A file mentioning only 'idea' four times would return count=4 and pass; a file covering all four topics on a single line would return count=1 and fail. The command does not reliably prove all four required topics are present.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f449672ba4e123120","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC1 proving command","norm_id":"n0fa8a6eeac27ab61","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A doc with 4+ lines containing 'idea' but missing parent_id/discovered_from/set-tags passes the check falsely","A doc covering all four topics in a dense paragraph (one line) fails the check despite being correct"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the bracketed count expression with:\n`rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `&& rg -q -- '--force' docs/concurrency.md` to the AC2 proving command so all three required elements (gate-exempt, plan-review, --force) are independently verified.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan body: '`--force` propagates up the cascade'","AC2 proving command: `rg -q 'gate-exempt' docs/concurrency.md && rg -q 'plan-review' docs/concurrency.md` — no check for '--force'"],"finding":"AC2's proving command checks for 'gate-exempt' and 'plan-review' but does not verify that `--force` propagation is documented, even though the plan body explicitly states that `--force` propagates up the cascade as a required content item.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7df13d4b65d1142f","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC2 proving command","norm_id":"n58f4aaccb653a2fa","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An agent adds the gate-exempt and plan-review text but omits the --force detail; AC2 passes without the full required content"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"`rg -q 'gate-exempt' docs/concurrency.md && rg -q 'plan-review' docs/concurrency.md && rg -q -- '--force' docs/concurrency.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extend the AC3 proving command to spot-check at least one or two of the four required semantic properties (e.g., `rg -q 'Jira' docs/event-schema.md && rg -q 'non-blocking' docs/event-schema.md`) in addition to the section header.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC3: 'docs/event-schema.md has a `## The session_log ticket type` section and does not defer session_log semantics to the root file'","Proving command: `rg -q '## The session_log ticket type' docs/event-schema.md` — only verifies the heading, not any semantic content"],"finding":"AC3's proving command only checks that the section header `## The session_log ticket type` exists, but the AC claim is broader: the section must cover four specific semantics (gate/lifecycle-exempt, graph/health-excluded, non-blocking links only, never Jira-synced) and must 'not defer session_log semantics to the root file'. A placeholder section with the correct heading but empty/deferring body would pass.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f50af9fae197d5693","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3 proving command","norm_id":"n34f780d6a7cd4fc6","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An agent adds a section header with a one-line stub that defers to CLAUDE.md; the proving command passes but the AC's substantive requirement is unmet"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"`rg -q '## The session_log ticket type' docs/event-schema.md && rg -q 'Jira' docs/event-schema.md && rg -q 'non-blocking' docs/event-schema.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Fix the AC1 proof command to verify *each* of the four terms independently (e.g., four separate `rg -q` checks ANDed together) so the script reliably confirms all four concepts are present.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["The verify step uses `rg -c` (line count for combined pattern) then `[ ... -ge 4 ]`, which checks quantity of matching lines, not presence of each individual term.","The criterion text says 'documents idea-status, hierarchy/containment, linking (relations + promotion), and the tags surface incl. --set-tags' — four distinct concepts each needing presence verification."],"finding":"The AC1 proof command uses `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` (which counts *lines* matching the combined alternation) and checks `-ge 4`, but this does not verify that all four terms are present — it only verifies at least 4 lines contain *any* of the four terms. A file with 4 lines each containing only 'idea' would pass; a file with all four terms on a single line would fail. The criterion's intent (all four concepts documented) is not reliably verified by this script.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f154be3f6c8ae70e7","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC1 proving command: `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md`","norm_id":"nd7ac5bd6a52359f8","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A file with 5 lines each containing 'idea' but missing 'parent_id', 'discovered_from', and 'set-tags' would pass the proof command yet violate the criterion.","A file with all four terms in a single-line table row would fail the proof command yet satisfy the criterion intent."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the single `rg -c` check with: `rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'event-schema' docs/ticket-model.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC1's proving command uses `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags'` with `-ge 4`, which counts lines matching ANY of the four patterns — four lines mentioning only 'idea' would satisfy the threshold without `parent_id`, `discovered_from`, or `set-tags` ever appearing. The command does not verify each concept is individually present.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2fa895763e33c7e2","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC1 proving command","norm_id":"n7590941e2dd312e0","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the count check with:\n`rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'event-schema' docs/ticket-model.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC3's proving command (`rg -q '## The session_log ticket type' docs/event-schema.md`) only checks for the section heading — a section that exists but contains no semantic content would pass, leaving the four listed semantics (gate/lifecycle-exempt, graph/health-excluded, non-blocking links only, never Jira-synced) unverified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb7041b7ae54918ad","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3 proving command","norm_id":"n62ea50ca6bc7eaa1","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"```\nrg -q '## The session_log ticket type' docs/event-schema.md \\\n  && rg -q 'lifecycle-exempt\\|gate-exempt' docs/event-schema.md \\\n  && rg -q 'non-blocking' docs/event-schema.md \\\n  && rg -q -i 'jira' docs/event-schema.md\n```","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The AC1 verify command uses `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` with a threshold of ≥4, but `rg -c` with an OR-regex counts total lines matching ANY term — so the check passes if 'idea' alone appears 4+ times, without requiring all four ticket-model concepts to be present. The stated requirement is that all four concepts (idea-status, hierarchy/containment, linking, tags) are documented.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa0b5529d5f276b60","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC1 proving command","norm_id":"n7e9685a9d7842e75","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the single `rg -c` check with four separate `rg -q` assertions, one per required concept term, so all four must be present for the AC to pass.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC1's proving command uses `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags'` (alternation) and asserts the count is >= 4. Because `-c` counts lines matching ANY of the four patterns, a document with four or more lines mentioning only 'idea' — and omitting the other three topics entirely — would satisfy the assertion. The command does not guarantee all four concept topics are present.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa287b0359c65819a","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — first AC, proving command","norm_id":"nb0c9958dd03fb774","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace `[ \"$(rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md)\" -ge 4 ]` with `rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md`.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC1's rg proving command uses a single OR-pattern with -c and -ge 4, meaning four lines all containing only 'idea' (and none containing 'parent_id', 'discovered_from', or 'set-tags') would satisfy the count check — so the command does NOT verify that all four concept topics are present.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3a2162dac9cac61a","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC1 proving command: `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` -ge 4","norm_id":"nd49e34af7b1141e9","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'event-schema' docs/ticket-model.md","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC1's proving command uses `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` with a single alternation pattern; `rg -c` counts total lines matching ANY of the alternatives, not one per pattern. A document mentioning only `idea` four times would return count≥4 and pass, even if `parent_id`, `discovered_from`, and `set-tags` are completely absent — leaving three of the four required concept topics unverified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc5753f10570a2f70","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC1 proving command","norm_id":"nc8dd670723e293e7","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'event-schema' docs/ticket-model.md","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC1's grep proof (`rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` ≥ 4) is satisfiable by four hits of the single term `idea` (or any one term). It does not verify that all four named concept topics (idea lifecycle, hierarchy/containment via parent_id, linking via discovered_from, tags via set-tags) are each present as distinct documented topics — the AC would pass if three of the four topics are entirely absent but `idea` appears four times.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe9da58eaf2876ed1","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC1 — 'Proving: test -f docs/ticket-model.md && [ \"$(rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md)\" -ge 4 ]'","norm_id":"n2ea243f162bd790e","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the single `-c … -ge 4` check with five separate `rg -q` assertions (one per required term/topic) chained with `&&`, so each topic is independently gated.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC1's shell proof (`rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md -ge 4`) counts lines matching ANY of the four terms, not that all four topics are substantively present. A file covering only 'idea' extensively (≥4 lines) with no mention of parent_id, discovered_from, or set-tags would still pass the grep while missing three of the four required topics.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f263b01ce558c2136","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria, AC1 — Proving shell command","norm_id":"nb1ced98724d4217c","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the `-c` count check with four separate `rg -q` checks joined by `&&`, one per required topic term, so each topic must be individually present.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define in the plan exactly which idea-status semantic dimensions `dispatch/gate/validate` names — e.g., '(1) excluded from `ready`/`next-batch` dispatch; (2) plan-review gate: ideas are not gate-exempt but `idea→closed` skips completion gates; (3) exempt from `validate` store-health findings' — and extend the AC grep to probe at least one term from each dimension.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'the four ticket-model concepts: the `idea` status lifecycle (dispatch/gate/`validate` semantics)'","CLAUDE.md 'idea' section uses `validate` to mean the MCP store-health command that exempts idea tickets from empty-epic/orphan/missing-description findings","CLAUDE.md 'idea' section: 'Excluded from dispatch (by omission). `idea` tickets never appear in `ready` or `next-batch`'","AC grep: `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags'` — `validate` and `dispatch` semantics are not probed, so a partial implementation passes the gate"],"finding":"The plan uses 'dispatch/gate/`validate` semantics' as a shorthand vocabulary for what docs/ticket-model.md must cover about the idea-status lifecycle, but never defines what these three terms mean in the rebar context. `dispatch` is not a rebar command (it refers to the ready/next-batch scheduling surfaces); `gate` is ambiguous (plan-review gate? claim gate? both?); `validate` refers to the MCP store-health tool. An implementer must reverse-engineer all three from CLAUDE.md. The AC grep (`rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags'`) does not include `validate` or the dispatch surfaces, so the doc could be delivered missing that dimension and still pass.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f848f705a8e67999b","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'docs/ticket-model.md' bullet; AC line 1 (Proving shell command)","norm_id":"n27bc7c7a6a8ff6c6","priority":0.4813,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Doc author writes ticket-model.md covering idea lifecycle transitions but omits the `validate` exemption and the `ready`/`next-batch` exclusion, yet still passes all 4 grep matches and all ACs.","Different authors interpret `gate` differently — one covers the plan-review gate, another covers the claim gate, a third covers both."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the shorthand with an explicit enumeration in the plan: 'the `idea` status lifecycle: (a) `ready`/`next-batch` exclusion (dispatch), (b) completion-gate skip on `idea→closed` but plan-review gate still applies, (c) `validate` store-health exemption (empty-epic/orphan/missing-description/count findings suppressed).' Add `rg -q 'ready\\|next-batch\\|validate' docs/ticket-model.md` to the AC proof.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["1 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable)."],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add required cross-references in docs/ticket-model.md's spec (and a corresponding AC grep) to docs/concurrency.md (cascade gate) and docs/user-guide.md (auto-rotation) so agents can navigate from the concept doc to all related behavioral docs.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states ticket-model.md 'cross-references docs/event-schema.md for the underlying event mechanics'","Cascade gate interaction is placed in docs/concurrency.md and auto-rotation in docs/user-guide.md — neither is listed as a cross-ref target in ticket-model.md's spec","AC proving line only checks 'rg -q event-schema docs/ticket-model.md' — concurrency.md and user-guide.md links are not verified"],"finding":"docs/ticket-model.md's specified cross-references only name docs/event-schema.md; the plan does not require cross-references to docs/concurrency.md (for cascade gate interaction) or docs/user-guide.md (for auto-rotation), leaving agents who start from the ticket-model concept doc without a navigation path to those related behavioral docs.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9245cebfa0a536c5","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — docs/ticket-model.md description; AC line 1 (Proving grep)","norm_id":"n186b1db8bd21386c","priority":0.0943,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An agent consulting docs/ticket-model.md for the full ticket-model picture learns about linking/tags/hierarchy but finds no pointer to cascade gate semantics or session-log rotation, missing those behaviors entirely."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In the docs/ticket-model.md What-section description, add: 'It also cross-references docs/concurrency.md for cascade-gate interaction and docs/user-guide.md for session-log auto-rotation.' Update the AC proving line to: `rg -q 'event-schema' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'concurrency' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'user-guide' docs/ticket-model.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Retitle or add a subtitle to clarify that this story only creates the documentation destinations (e.g., 'Populate authoritative docs for CLAUDE.md ticket-model content (pre-S2)') so the title faithfully reflects the scoped-out root-file editing.","cohort":["E3","G5","T6"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Title: 'Re-home CLAUDE.md-native content into authoritative docs'","Scope section: 'Out: editing the root guidance file (that is S2, which replaces these sections with pointers)'","The body does LESS than the title promises: only the destination docs are created; the source is intentionally left untouched."],"finding":"The plan title says 're-home' (implying the content moves from CLAUDE.md to docs — i.e., source cleared + destination populated), but the plan body explicitly scopes out any editing of the root guidance file. An agent reading the title as the acceptance criterion would consider the work incomplete if CLAUDE.md still contains the original content after this story closes.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4d13d5f461c98dc3","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Title / Scope section ('Out: editing the root guidance file (that is S2…)')","norm_id":"na41299b749249bd7","priority":0.0754,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An agent (or reviewer) interprets 're-home' as a complete move and flags the story incomplete because CLAUDE.md still holds the original content.","A downstream agent picking up S2 misunderstands its starting state, expecting CLAUDE.md to already be slimmed."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Rename to: 'Populate authoritative docs for ticket-model content (destination step; root-file removal is S2)' and/or add a one-line note at the top of the AC section: 'Note: CLAUDE.md is NOT edited in this story — that is S2.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Correct the 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed' premise: `docs/user-guide.md` already has a `### The \\`idea\\` status` section — clarify that `docs/ticket-model.md` will carry the *agent-facing* concept doc (e.g., dispatch/gate/validate semantics, Jira round-trip, the MCP `create_idea` atomic genesis) while cross-referencing `user-guide.md` for the user-facing walkthrough, rather than re-homing content that already has a home.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed'","docs/user-guide.md lines 85–98: '### The `idea` status — a parking lot for undesigned work' — full semantics already documented","CLAUDE.md lines 74–108: agent-facing `idea` semantics also documented there","The plan's AC for ticket-model.md checks for presence of 'idea' with rg but never checks for duplication or cross-referencing of user-guide.md"],"finding":"The plan's Design Decisions section asserts 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed,' but docs/user-guide.md already contains a named `### The \\`idea\\` status — a parking lot for undesigned work` section (lines 85–98) documenting the key semantics: structurally unclaimable, excluded from `ready`/`next-batch`, promote via `transition idea open`, and `idea → closed` skips completion gates. This false premise affects how the implementer scopes `docs/ticket-model.md` — they may believe the `idea` section is a net-new agent-facing document when user-guide.md already covers it (for users), and may produce a ticket-model.md that either duplicates that section or omits cross-referencing it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0429b48b788a9b12","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Design decisions section: 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed'","norm_id":"n94d77fe461abcf3e","priority":0.3187,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer writes docs/ticket-model.md treating `idea` semantics as net-new, producing content that duplicates docs/user-guide.md §idea without cross-referencing it — introducing drift risk.","Implementer conflates 'unhomed in docs/ for agents' with 'wholly undocumented,' missing that user-guide.md already carries a version of this content and that ticket-model.md needs to be differentiated (e.g., agent-specific nuances vs. user-facing CLI walkthrough)."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In the Design Decisions section, replace 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed' with something like: 'only the `idea` status lacks an agent-facing concept doc — `docs/user-guide.md` covers the user-facing CLI walkthrough, but the agent-specific semantics (dispatch/gate exemption, MCP `create_idea` atomic genesis, Jira `IDEA` round-trip) have no dedicated home in `docs/`.' Also add to the `docs/ticket-model.md` AC a requirement to cross-reference `docs/user-guide.md §idea` rather than duplicate it.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Correct the 'Design decisions' rationale: note that docs/user-guide.md already documents the `idea` status for human users (lines 85–108), so docs/ticket-model.md should cross-reference it rather than re-document it from scratch, and the 'wholly unhomed' claim should be narrowed to the agent-facing dispatch/gate/validate semantics that user-guide.md does NOT cover.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states: 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed. So the new `docs/ticket-model.md` carries the agent-facing *concept* with cross-refs'","docs/user-guide.md lines 85–108: '### The `idea` status — a parking lot for undesigned work' section exists with substantive content about the status, `rebar idea` command, and `idea open` promotion","ABSENCE of any cross-reference between the planned ticket-model.md and the existing user-guide.md idea section"],"finding":"The 'Design decisions' section asserts 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed' in docs/, but docs/user-guide.md already contains a dedicated `### The \\`idea\\` status — a parking lot for undesigned work` section (lines 85–108) covering the parking-lot concept, `rebar idea` command, and `idea → open` promotion. An implementer relying on this claim may write docs/ticket-model.md as if idea is entirely new to docs/, duplicating content already in user-guide.md without adding a cross-reference — producing drift between the two files.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd06a097b56a6c9eb","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Design decisions section — 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed'","norm_id":"n5e928cdb4eda4ddf","priority":0.3187,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer authors docs/ticket-model.md with a full idea-status description, not knowing user-guide.md already covers it, creating two divergent canonical descriptions of the same behavior.","A reader following docs/README.md to ticket-model.md for idea-status semantics gets a different (potentially stale) description than the one in user-guide.md."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In the 'Design decisions' section, replace 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed' with 'the `idea` status has user-facing coverage in docs/user-guide.md but lacks agent-facing dispatch/gate/validate semantics in docs/; docs/ticket-model.md should cross-reference user-guide.md for the basic parking-lot concept and add only the agent-specific semantics (structurally unclaimable, excluded from ready/next-batch, validate exemptions).'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Before writing the `--force` cascade behavior into `docs/concurrency.md`, verify in `src/rebar/_commands/claim.py` (`claim_compute`) and `_resolve_open_parent` whether `--force` is actually propagated to parent claims during the cascade, and document only the verified behavior.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states: 'docs/concurrency.md (the I4a cascade section) additionally documents the cascade's gate interaction: a cascaded parent claim runs the parent's own plan-review claim gate; epics/stories are not gate-exempt; --force propagates up the cascade.'","docs/concurrency.md I4a section (lines 97-119) describes the cascade in detail but makes NO mention of --force interaction or gate behavior.","docs/plan-review-gate.md line 51-52 documents --force at the leaf level ('--force=\"<reason>\" bypasses it') but does not describe whether it propagates during a cascade.","ABSENCE: No existing doc confirms or denies whether --force on a child claim causes --force to be passed to the cascaded parent claim."],"finding":"The concurrency.md gate-interaction section will assert that '--force propagates up the cascade', but this specific behavior (--force flag propagation during the parent-first cascade) is not documented anywhere in existing docs and the plan does not direct the implementer to verify it against source code (claim.py / _resolve_open_parent) before writing it as authoritative documentation.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fdebbdbfca9dbe632","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / docs/concurrency.md AC: `rg -q 'gate-exempt' docs/concurrency.md && rg -q 'plan-review' docs/concurrency.md`","norm_id":"n5980372549f27c8d","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer writes 'force propagates up the cascade' as authoritative fact in concurrency.md; if the actual implementation does NOT propagate --force (i.e., --force only bypasses the gate at the originally-claimed ticket, not its cascaded parents), the new doc is actively wrong and misleads agents about how to bypass gates on cascaded parents.","An agent reads the new docs/concurrency.md and uses --force expecting gate bypass on a parent claim, but the parent claim still hits the plan-review gate because --force was not actually propagated up."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a note in the What/Design-decisions section: 'The --force cascade propagation claim must be verified against claim.py:_resolve_open_parent before writing; if --force is not propagated, document the actual behavior (force applies only to the leaf ticket, not cascaded parents).'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to the plan's description of the concurrency.md gate-interaction section the decision rule: the gate fires per-ticket inside `claim_compute` before the parent-cascade recursion, so each ancestor in the cascade is independently gated (and `--force` propagates up because `force_plan_review` is threaded through every recursive call).","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'a cascaded parent claim runs the parent's own plan-review claim gate; epics/stories are not gate-exempt; --force propagates up the cascade'","src/rebar/_commands/claim.py lines 126-153: plan_review_precheck(ticket_id, ...) fires BEFORE the parent-cascade block, and the recursive claim_compute call also calls plan_review_precheck for the parent ticket_id","src/rebar/_commands/gates.py line 93-94: only bug/session_log/code_review/identity are exempt; epics and stories are not","The plan does not state whether the gate fires once (at the leaf) or per-ticket in the cascade"],"finding":"The plan specifies that docs/concurrency.md must document the cascade's gate interaction including 'a cascaded parent claim runs the parent's own plan-review claim gate,' but does not specify the decision rule about gate-fire order within the cascade: the gate fires individually per ticket inside claim_compute (before the parent-cascade recursion), meaning BOTH the child and every ancestor are gated separately — not just the initial target. A doc author reading only the plan may document this as 'the gate runs once on the top-level claim,' missing that the gate fires on each cascaded ancestor independently.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fefc89a8c9b278fa6","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'docs/concurrency.md (the I4a cascade section)' bullet; Acceptance Criteria line 2","norm_id":"nccf89cbfe005a2bc","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Doc author writes 'the cascade gate checks the ticket being claimed' (true but incomplete), omitting that each ancestor is independently gated as claim_compute recurses.","An agent reads the new concurrency.md and concludes that `--force` on a child bypasses the gate for the child only, not for cascaded ancestors — missing the recursive force_plan_review propagation in claim.py line 147."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The AC proving command `rg -q -- '--force' docs/concurrency.md` is a false-positive verifier: `--force` is already present in the existing concurrency.md text as a substring of `--force-with-lease=<ref>:<old>` (I6 section, reconciler CAS lock description). An implementer who omits the '`--force` propagates up the cascade' gate-interaction content would still pass this AC check, making the criterion unverifiable as written.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7c8c8d64024d7f05","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — `docs/concurrency.md` proving command: `rg -q -- '--force' docs/concurrency.md`","norm_id":"n9c70f1b0c405efc8","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace `rg -q -- '--force' docs/concurrency.md` with `rg -q 'force.*propagat\\|propagat.*cascade.*force' docs/concurrency.md` or similar pattern that only matches the new cascade/gate content and cannot be satisfied by `--force-with-lease`.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"no","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan's AC4 states docs/user-guide.md should document session-log auto-rotation 'alongside its existing capture-helper section,' implying user-guide.md already has a capture-helper section. In fact, the capture-helper detail (`.rebar/current_session_log` pointer, `rebar.append_session_log`, the auto-rotation semantics) lives in CLAUDE.md (lines 217-242). docs/user-guide.md has only a 3-command 'Session logs — durable working notes' stub (lines 163-173) with no capture-helper content. The 'existing' anchor the plan relies on for placement does not exist in user-guide.md.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f37a421c9cf9998f8","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section, fourth bullet: 'alongside its existing capture-helper section'; AC4 Proving line","norm_id":"n8800c2f1b8c5317b","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace 'alongside its existing capture-helper section' with 'by expanding the existing minimal session-log stub (lines 163-173) into a full capture-helper section that also covers the `.rebar/current_session_log` pointer and session fingerprint auto-rotation behavior.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan's 'Design decisions' section asserts 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed,' but docs/user-guide.md already has a named section '### The `idea` status — a parking lot for undesigned work' (lines 85-99), docs/jira-sync-setup.md has '## The `idea` status ↔ Jira `IDEA`' (line 481), and docs/cli-reference.md has a dedicated `idea` subsection (line 194). This premise is false, meaning the plan's rationale for what docs/ticket-model.md must carry new content about vs. cross-reference is built on an incorrect baseline scan — the idea status is already multi-homed across user-guide.md, cli-reference.md, and jira-sync-setup.md.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ff4ceb03ac87279cf","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Design decisions section: 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed'","norm_id":"nab5c694f77e0bb0f","priority":0.3187,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace 'only the `idea` status is wholly unhomed' with 'the `idea` status is documented in user-guide.md and cli-reference.md for users but lacks a consolidated agent-facing concept doc; ticket-model.md will serve as that agent-facing reference and cross-reference the existing user-facing docs.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"662c44b2473054f9","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":213.4,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":572561.6,"total_ms":572876.9,"verify_requests":24},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de5